  "description": "Japanese quail (Coturnix japonica) raised for eggs and meat. Sexual maturity at 6 weeks, producing 300+ eggs per year at 10-12g each. The smallest and fastest-reproducing poultry species, requiring minimal space (25x25 cm cage per bird) and feed (20-25g/day).",
